Commands: git rm <file>
          git reset HEAD
          git checkout .
          git reflog

A files removal updates with a command (git rm <file>), otherwise, the file's absent in the update. Normal file removal never appears in the current HEAD without git's aid.

git rm <file>
Notes: Unlike normal file structures, a file reversion exists with Github (git reset HEAD, git checkout). If a commit already occured, then a reference log (git reflog) is the reversion method.




